rComments: Dr. Overcash is the swaggiest teacher in all of Champaign-Urbana. His knowledge of chemistry is only overshadowed by his knowledge of chemistry cat memes. This dude brought sexyback after JT. He is the truth.

Now I really, really...REALLY hate chemistry. however Dr. Overcash made it bareable. he was very nice and very clear on everything he taught and was able to help me with ease when i went to office hours, he was my favorite professor

Great professor who genuinely cares about his students and explains chemical concepts really well. Lectures can get boring sometimes, but the clicker questions in class are very helpful and similar to those on quizzes/exams.

Cares more about your grade then you do. He puts so many resources on his website to help you learn. I hate chemistry but Overcash makes you want to learn and does it in a great way. One of my favorite professors in my least favorite class.

Overcash completely turned around my perception of this class. Made it very interesting, and was extremely helpful and accessible. Plus he had some jokes that were so bad, you had to laugh at them. Kept a very light atmosphere in the class.

Overcash was an average professor. First few exams were straight foward and easy. Third exam (Thermo) he failed to deliver the material correctly. Class average on the exam was 13/25. Final exam was a average in difficulty. Class average was a 60% onthe final. Class was tough but he curved the entire lass 8% or 80 points out of 1000. Don't pick him

He was very hard to understand and read straight from the power points. His quizzes and mock exams were nothing like the real exams. The exams were very confusing and way harder than the mock exams when he said they would be similar. Did not enjoy his class at all.

Dr. Overcash was a great professor. Really cared about the material, had a lot of fun, and was always willing to help. He had to deal with a lot of bull from people in the class who were plain rude or loud in lecture, and did it well. It's a shame that all those people say he was a horrible professor. He definitely taught me chemistry.
He was not very helpful in lecture and mostly just read off the power point slides, which made it difficult to write the lab reports.

Beware, Chem 101 is not an easy class for someone who hates science. Labs, lon-capa, and bookwork will take over your whole week. Tests are pretty complicated and hard to study for. I was able to understand what happened in lecture but I didn't do great on the tests. Discussions didn't help me much either. Take an easier science class if you can.
Best teacher I ever had. Also very young and hot!!!!

Overcash is a really good guy, who you can tell is very passionate about chem. That being said, he isn't the greatest teacher. He was consistently unclear in lecture, not very helpful (when asking for help), and had an obsession with blowing things up (which, while cool, was extremely annoying at 8 in the morning). Basic material, harder tests.

The lectures are extremely boring and it is hard to follow most of the time. He does tons of demos and blows alot of stuff up so if you like that then its a good class but at 8am it was just annoying. I thought the tests were really easy but other people had trouble with them. He isn't that bad though

Overcash is a nice guy who seems to truely love what he is teaching, but he is very inexperienced at being a lecturer. At times he is very hard to follow and I found myself getting lost easily. He blows things up a lot, almost too much. I did not like his class at all and the tests were tricky. But he is a nice guy who loves chemistry.

Overcash is a great teacher who definitely appears to care about whether the students understand what is going on. He show really cool demo's and blows things up a lot which is cool. The class isn't hard which was expected because it is very basic material but the teaching is great although tests may have confusing questions.
Good TA. Grades on time, pretty nice, and explains things clearly. They should hire more TAs like John. As for the course itself...well it was okay...

John is a very good TA for Chemistry 104.  The class is definitely rigorous because Professor Ray covers a lot of material in a short amount of time and relies on the TAs a lot to relay the information to students.  John, however, was one of the better TAs.  He actually held good review sessions and was always there to help if we needed it.
Quality teacher. He got it done for me.
